  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient has given written informed consent to participate in the study in accordance
             with local regulations

          -  Adult patients 18 years and older with a diagnosis of T1D made at least 1 year prior
             to informed consent

          -  Patients are being treated with insulin or insulin analog delivered via CSII or MDI

          -  Willing and able to perform SMBG and complete the study diary as required per protocol

          -  At the Screening Visit, A1C must be between 7.0% to 11.0%

          -  Females of childbearing potential must use an adequate method of contraception and
             have a negative pregnancy test

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Use of antidiabetic agent other than insulin or insulin analog at the time of
             screening

          -  Use of sodium-glucose cotransporter (SGLT) inhibitors within 8 weeks prior to
             screening

          -  Chronic systemic corticosteroid use

          -  Type 2 diabetes mellitus (T2DM), or severely uncontrolled T1D as determined by the
             Investigator
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
